<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-289-344  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 289 344.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  April 12 1989 n104 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Haggling starts for 1-2-3 users. (Lotus 1-2-3 software priceincrease)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (prices).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (prices).andO;Topic:     Price IncreasesDiscountVendor RelationsSpreadsheetsDealers and Agents.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Haggling starts for 1-2-3 users A rise in the dealer price of Lotus 1-2-3means users will find discounts from the list price harder to come by.andM;Although Lotus has announced a rise in its dealer price for 1-2-3, it saysthe recommended retail price remains unchanged.andP;  According to a Lotusspokesperson, customers buying at the full retail price should not beaffected by the price change.andM;However, he warned that users accustomed to heavy discounts from theirdealers could no longer necessarily count on them continuing at the samelevel.andP;  &quot;This will vary from dealer to dealer,&quot; said the spokesperson,&quot;depending on the relationship between dealer and customer.&quot;andM;The spokesperson justified the cutting of dealer margins saying the companywas employing more sales and support staff to back up the retail channel.andM;Both the new Release 2.2 of 1-2-3, due out in the third quarter, and Rellease3, scheduled in July, will be priced at pound sterling 395.andP;  However, theprice of Release 3 will rise to pound sterling 475 after December 31.andM;Users who bought earlier releases between the beginning of last September and30 days after the first shipment of the relevent later release will be ableto upgrade for pound sterling 35.andP;  Users who purchased before last Septemberwill require pound sterling 140 to upgrade.andO;</TEXT></DOC>